The Bride's Cave
[vignette dungeons/brides_cave]

Weathered boards cover the entrance, a faded warning painted in red: "SEALED BY ORDER - NO ENTRY." Through gaps you glimpse limestone chambers stretching into darkness. You carefully pry away the boards and squeeze inside.

It is pitch black inside.

The air is cold, damp, and silent.

choices:

* Venture deeper into the cave = Pick a passage and see where it leads
  @if has brass_lantern {
    You light the old **brass lantern**, it gutters briefly before casting a flickering glow on the limestone walls of the cavern. You notice immediately that the walls have a peculiar hatched texture.

    You choose a passage at random and press forward.
    +open "A Record in Stone"
  } @else {
    You stumble in the dark, trying to make your way by feel. You crack you head on a low overhang and curse. There's no way you can navigate this cave without a light. Slowly and with great care, you feel your way back to the entrance, and find the stack of boards you removed when you came in. You press the boards back into place behind you, lest another traveller make the same mistake as you.
    +flee_dungeon
  }
  
